                  <persName id="t18130915-17-person199">
                  JANE 
                  PILKINGTON
               <interp inst="t18130915-17-person199" type="surname" value="PILKINGTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18130915-17-person199" type="given" value="JANE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18130915-17-person199" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I <rs id="t18130915-17-viclabel93" type="occupation">deal in second hand clothes</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18130915-17-victim198 t18130915-17-viclabel93"></join>. On Saturday last, between nine and ten in the morning, the prisoner came to my shop; he agreed to buy two shirts for eight shillings, two pair of stockings for three shillings, and a waistcoat at seven shillings and sixpence. He told me to fold them up; he would pay me for them. I folded them up; he seemed to feel in his pocket for the money. In a little time I turned my head of one side, he throwed a quantity of snuff in my face. He took the bundle and ran away. He was pursued and taken, and brought back with the property.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18130915-17-person200">
